25:46.081 --> 25:52.250
Administration has been very active in real 
development since its inception. And The real

25:54.944 --> 26:13.583
problem that they face now is there are a lot of 
people who feel it's not fair that rural electrics

25:54.944 --> 26:13.583
can loan money at a lower rate and therefore, in a 
sense, be subsidized while other power companies

25:54.944 --> 26:13.583
can't. Now, once the system was built, the 
maintenance problems aren't as expensive as they

26:14.364 --> 26:20.530
were when it was first put in. My wife was raised out 
in west Texas on a ranch, and they didn't get

26:20.999 --> 26:27.805
electricity until the mid-50s. Had it not been for 
REA, they still wouldn't have electricity. It's

26:31.729 --> 26:32.930
impossible. You just really can't quantify that 
in any isolated area, which west Texas is isolated

26:32.950 --> 26:48.964
by distance, and Appalachia by the wrinkled 
mountains and the terrain. And so wherever there

26:49.855 --> 27:00.256
was a problem that made provision of electric 
current not economical going the private way,

26:49.855 --> 27:00.256
this is the only way they could do it. But that need 
is really not as much as it is, and there's been a

27:00.798 --> 27:11.239
constant force in Congress to reduce the subsidy 
that goes in that direction. You mentioned that

27:12.485 --> 27:14.026
you retired in 1986. And what have you seen since 
